Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球又一次的被卷入到一场浩劫中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Earth was suddenly caught in the cross fire once again.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第六大地球灾难时刻{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Number six on our countdown of worst days...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.30,0:07:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳系后期重轰炸期{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Late Heavy Bombardment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在忒伊亚撞击过去约一亿五千万年后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Approximately 150 million years after the Theia impact,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地壳冷却了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the Earth's crust cooled.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.89,0:08:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一些人推测 早期大洋甚至生命或已形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some speculate that early oceans and even life may have evolved.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.64,0:08:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但另一场大灾难将把这一切切摧毁殆尽{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But another cataclysm would wipe the slate clean.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.90,0:08:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在太阳系的边缘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the far reaches of the Solar System{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.57,0:08:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}外太阳系的巨大气体行星轨道开始波动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the orbit of the outer gas giants began to fluctuate{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.53,0:08:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}干扰了大量的彗星以及小行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}disrupting vast swarms of asteroids and comets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数兆颗小行星脱离了原始轨道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Trillions broke loose from their orbits{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且朝着一颗布满岩石的行星冲来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and plunged inward towards the rocky planets,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}开始了一段炙热的毁灭浩劫{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}launching an era of fiery destruction{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.39,0:08:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是我们所知的后期重轰炸期{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}known as the late heavy bombardment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.61,0:08:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们知道有德州大小的陨石撞上地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We know asteroids of the size of Texas hit the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.27,0:08:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}任何该体积的陨石撞击都会导致大洋的消失{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Any impact that big causes the entire ocean to go away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.43,0:08:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球一次又一次的变成不毛之地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We sterilize the Earth over and over and over{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.98,0:08:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们推断 地球上的生命不断进化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so the inference we have is that life evolved over and over and over{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是总是被这些陨石冲击所摧毁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just to be snuffed down again by these large impacts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无休止的陨石轰炸形成了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The relentless bombardment gouged down craters{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.46,0:09:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数千英里宽的环形山{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}thousands of miles wide{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而这些陨石冲击持续了至少两亿年之久{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the hits just kept coming for at least 200 million years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.51,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}今日 历经数十亿年的侵蚀和板块运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Today, billions of years of erosion and shifting plaque tectonics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当年那些陨石冲击的痕迹已经消失{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}have erased any trace of the cataclysm from the Earth's surface.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但在月球上的环形山就不一样了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But it is a different story on the crater face of the Moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.42,0:09:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以很清楚的看到月球表面上的痕迹{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can see very clearly its record on the face of the Moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.49,0:09:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}熔岩区就是在这次巨大冲击下形成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The lava field basins were formed during the giant impact events{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是在地球的后期重轰炸期{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that occurred during the late heavy bombardment{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们便知在这期间有大型物体撞击地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so we know that large objects hit the Earth during this time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.01,0:09:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是这些天国的怒火{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But this celestial reign of fire{\r}
